@node Install "Installation"
                                 @{b}Installation@{ub}
                                ==============

A.Use The Auto Installer..

if not then goto B:

B.Copy  Zip-RecoVer Folder to Where ever You Want But Keep  all the files,
In Same Drawer.

C.make sure you have  assign ZipRecover: Device:point out your zip recover directory
           as example assign ZipRecover: Programs:Apps/ZipRecover/


@endnode




@node usage "usage"
                                 @{b}Usage@{ub}
           (1) - > WordList:
                   ---------
               - > Actual Progress of WordList RecoVer is an Soft RecoVer
               - > Basicly list All The Password You USE Most of the time
               - > see included WrdBox/Pwlist & List Your Passwords Down
               - > & Save it As what ever Filename You Like long as You can
               - > Remmember To Save/Copy/Move the file to ZipRecover:WrdFiles/

           (2) - > FileName .Zip
                   -------------
               - > Copy Your .Zip Archive to ZipRecover:ZipFiles/



           (4) - > example Usage
                   -------------
                 1. Run Zip-RecoVer
                 2. Load filename.Zip  from ZipRecover:ZipFiles/ Folder

                 3. Select a filename from openned .zip list.

                 4. Double Click on Load WordList File & Select One..
                              ==============
                 5.Enable FUNZIP if you want Progress & Try Same Time..

		 6.Start & Enjoy the progress..

@endnode

